<UserControl
    x:Class="UITests.Shared.Windows_UI_Xaml_Automation.UiaStaleCells_DataGrid"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
    xmlns:local="using:UITests.Shared.Windows_UI_Xaml_Automation"
    xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    d:DesignHeight="600"
    d:DesignWidth="600"
    mc:Ignorable="d">

    <ScrollViewer>
        <StackPanel Padding="20" Spacing="16">

            <TextBlock
                AutomationProperties.HeadingLevel="Level1"
                Style="{ThemeResource TitleTextBlockStyle}"
                Text="UIA Stale-Cells Repro (DataGrid pattern)" />

            <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords">
                Repro for: Accessibility/Automation – DataGridRow contents display empty cells after an action that
                refreshes the data (#492). The 'MiniGrid' below replicates the WCT DataGrid automation shape with
                minimal custom controls: a grid peer whose children are per-item virtual peers
                (like DataGridItemAutomationPeer), each delegating its cells to the currently-realized row container
                and calling OwningRowPeer.InvalidatePeer() — exactly as DataGridItemAutomationPeer.GetChildrenCore does.
            </TextBlock>

            <TextBlock
                Margin="0,8,0,0"
                AutomationProperties.HeadingLevel="Level2"
                Style="{ThemeResource SubtitleTextBlockStyle}"
                Text="How to verify the fix" />

            <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords">
                1. Open inspect.exe / Accessibility Insights and point it at 'MiniGrid' below.
                2. Expand a row item — you should see its cell text (e.g. "Row 0 — v1").
                3. Click "Refresh data". Each row's cells are rebuilt with new content ("… — v2", "… — v3", …).
                4. Re-inspect the SAME row item.
                Bug:      the row item still reports the old cells, or empty cells (the realized content is detached).
                Expected: the row item reports the current cell text, matching what is visible on screen.
            </TextBlock>

            <Border
                Padding="12"
                Background="{ThemeResource CardBackgroundFillColorDefaultBrush}"
                BorderBrush="{ThemeResource CardStrokeColorDefaultBrush}"
                BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4">
                <StackPanel Spacing="8">
                    <Button
                        x:Name="RefreshButton"
                        AutomationProperties.Name="RefreshData"
                        Content="Refresh data" />
                    <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource BodyStrongTextBlockStyle}" Text="MiniGrid (inspect this)" />
                    <ContentControl
                        x:Name="MiniGridHost"
                        HorizontalContentAlignment="Stretch"
                        AutomationProperties.AutomationId="MiniGrid"
                        AutomationProperties.Name="MiniGrid" />
                </StackPanel>
            </Border>

        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</UserControl>
